        "title": "fix: use target default branch in repair plans",
        "body": "## Summary\n- hydrate repair plans from the target repository default branch instead of assuming main\n- preserve `target_branch` through repair-comment-router dispatch before worker checkout\n- cover non-main default branches, target-branch config, workflow dispatch plumbing, and worker checkout behavior in repair tests\n\nFixes #252.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm run format && pnpm run build:repair && node --test test/repair/comment-router-config.test.ts test/repair/workflow-sparse-checkout.test.ts test/repair/plan-cluster.test.ts test/repair/run-worker.test.ts`\n- `pnpm run check`\n\n## Proof\nFocused regression proof for the review finding:\n\n```text\n✔ comment router config preserves target branch from dispatch args\n✔ repair comment router workflow preserves repository dispatch target branch\n✔ plan-cluster hydrates the repository default branch instead of hard-coding main\n✔ run-worker starts Codex in the target checkout when one is available\n```\n\nFull local check also passed:\n\n```text\npnpm run check\n...\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n",
